==English==

===Adjective===
'''acute'''
# Urgent, as ''his need for medical attention was acute''
# Intense, as ''she had an acute sense of honor''
# (''[[geometry|geom.]]'') Sharp, as in an angle less than 90 degrees.
#:antonym: [[obtuse]]
# (''[[geometry|geom.]]'') A triangle composed of acute angles.
# (''[[medicine]]'') Describes an abnormal condition of recent or sudden onset. Does not imply severity (unlike in common usage).
#:antonym: [[chronic]]

